How We Detect Polymarket Insiders

Not all large trades are insider trades.

We use a multi signal scoring system to separate real Polymarket insiders from regular whales.

Every trade on Polymarket is scanned and scored across five signals.

Size Anomaly
-> Trade is 10 times or more larger than the wallet average
-> Sudden outsized bet

Account Freshness
-> Wallet created recently (less than 7 days)
-> Potential burner account

Dormancy Wakeup
-> Wallet inactive for 30 days or more
-> Suddenly places a large trade

Price Conviction
-> Large position at very low odds (below 20 cents)
-> High conviction contrarian bet

Low Trade Count
-> Wallet has fewer than 10 total trades
-> Likely single purpose account

Each signal is weighted and combined into a suspicion score from 0 to 100.

> Trades scoring above 35 are flagged as potential insider activity.

